<TEXT>
nineteen states have taken steps to change laws that govern the 
guardians who take on the personal and financial affairs of old 
people aiming to close loopholes and prevent abuse of the 
elderlys rights 
almost all the action has come since publication last fall of 
associated press stories about shortcomings in the littleknown but 
powerful system of guardianship under which hundreds of thousands 
of people deemed mentally incompetent have had their affairs turned 
over to someone else 
the series guardians of the elderly an ailing system 
which examined guardianship laws from a national viewpoint and in 
each of the 50 states and the district of columbia found a network 
of overburdened courts that routinely fail to monitor wards under 
their jurisdiction which often opens the door to physical and 
financial mistreatment 
legislation to strengthen guardianship protections has been 
introduced in arizona california colorado florida michigan new 
jersey ohio oklahoma and pennsylvania us rep claude pepper 
dfla has drafted a national reform law 
in addition studies of guardianship laws are under way in new 
york virginia mississippi and illinois court procedural changes 
have been made in alaska pennsylvania and washington state and 
the idaho senate is considering a resolution for a study 
five new laws in new mexico have already provided 755000 to 
set up private guardianship services adult protective services 
social workers inhome care and homemaker help for frail elderly 
and disabled adults and a demonstration program for counseling the 
elderly on guardianship medicaid and nursing home financial issues 
the indiana general assembly this year amended the state 
guardianship law based on recommendations from a longterm review 
by the probate code study commission the changes included 
requiring biannual review of a wards personal status in addition 
to his or her financial reports and increasing legal 
representation for the ward 
and earlier this month utah gov norm bangerter signed into law 
a package of guardianship reforms that was approved unanimously at 
the state house 
the reforms will require among other things that proposed 
wards receive written notice of guardianship proceedings that they 
be represented in proceedings by attorneys and that clear and 
convincing medical evidence be provided to prove incapacity in 
lieu of such catchall phrases as advanced age or 
confinement 
betty tatham chairwoman of the 21member panel that overhauled 
utahs guardianship law said the task force drew heavily on the 
aps guardianship research state and national in identifying 
problems with the states existing law and drafting the new one 
we want the state of utah to be a good place for retired 
people to live we think that this bill will have a positive impact 
on protecting the elderly in our society bangerter said 
in virginia a house committee earlier this month defeated a 
proposal to remove advanced age from state law as a reason to 
place a person under guardianship physicians in general 
disapprove of such terminology saying that it makes it too easy to 
link advanced age with incompetency without other factors 
considered 
but an opponent delegate clinton miller argued the change 
wasnt needed because virginia requires expert testimony on the 
persons mental or physical incapacity the ap stories on 
guardianship in virginia however found that expert testimony was 
often nothing more than a oneparagraph statement from a doctor in 
85 percent of the cases examined such brief statements were all 
that was used to establish incompetency 
concerning the states with proposed legislation 
two bills to amend arizona guardianship laws received almost 
unanimous support in committee but have been delayed by the 
impeachment trial of gov evan mecham one would require guardians 
to file annual reports on the wellbeing of wards the other would 
remove advanced age as a reason to declare a person 
incapacitated 
california lawmakers said the ap series prompted several new 
bills in the state assembly they would variously certify 
professional guardians require counties to educate guardians on 
their responsibilities and require petitions seeking guardianship 
to spell out what the elderly person is capable of doing and what 
the guardian would handle 
colorado gov roy romer is expected to sign a bill which he 
received march 8 that would require guardians to supervise their 
wards more closely its sponsors said the legislation was prompted 
by the ap state series on colorados lack of required review of 
guardianship cases 
both houses in florida are considering legislation to 
dramatically liberalize state guardianship statutes it would 
require more accountability from guardians attorneys examining 
committees doctors and courts 
the michigan senate is considered two housepassed bills one 
would require legal representation for proposed wards and periodic 
judicial review of cases to see if guardianship remains necessary 
the second bill would prohibit nursing homes from requiring 
residents to have guardians 
a new jersey senate committee has passed a bill that would 
require courtappointed attorneys to report every two years on what 
they have done for their wards other legislation pending in the 
legislature would require annual reports 
marie muhler who runs the states yearold public guardian 
office said judges began clamping down after the ap series i 
notice now that some courts are putting in strict guidelines for 
accounting she said in an interview 
the ohio senate may vote in may on its rewritten version of a 
housepassed bill overhauling state guardianship laws the proposal 
would limit the definition of incompetent by removing the term 
advanced age and require the appointment of investigators to check 
each case of alleged incompetency and explain their rights to the 
proposed wards 
an oklahoma joint conference committee is considering a bill 
that would change the state guardianship law to require more 
reporting and improve legal representation 
in pennsylvania legislation now in committee would refine the 
definition of incapacity provide lawyers for incompetent people 
without them and set regular review hearings the bills sponsor 
rep allen kukovich says similar legislation failed to reach the 
assembly floor in recent years but that this bill has better 
chances because of the ap series and the attention it brought to 
guardianship 
studies of guardianship laws are underway in several states 
in virginia such an overall study continues in the general 
assembly despite the defeat of the proposal to change wording in 
the existing law the study will also cover other protective 
services for the elderly and incapacitated 
the mississippi council on aging and the cook county public 
guardians office in chicago report they are working on 
guardianship improvements court officials in alaska washington 
state and pennsylvania say they have made some changes in 
guardianship procedures since the ap series 
a study of new yorks guardianship system called 
conservatorship is rather well along and findings may be 
available this summer according to the states top administrative 
judge albert rosenblatt the study was prompted by the attention 
the ap gave the issue rosenblatt said 
</TEXT>
