campaign events are an extraordinarily unreliable guide to 
election results jackson drew big crowds in 1984 and still 
finished third in the democratic presidential race that year 
but the rallies and town meetings and handshaking tours can be a 
window into the reality of the campaign and into how the voters are 
reacting 
